    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# 1. Statistical Mistakes\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tCsC3uukyfeU"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 1.1. Inadecuate Control"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ocirdbTUyvig"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Imagine we want to test whether a short training program improves participants’ performance on a task. People often get better simply from practicing the task, even without any training. If we measure only one group before and after the program, we might wrongly conclude that the training worked. By including a proper control group, we can see whether improvements are truly due to the training or just to practice over time."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VlksTHiZ5HF0"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Example: Spurious intervention effect without a control group\n",
        "\n",
        "We simulate:\n",
        "\n",
        "Practice effect → everyone improves slightly over time.\n",
        "\n",
        "Training → actually has no real effect.\n",
        "\n",
        "Without a control group → looks like training works.\n",
        "\n",
        "With a control group → shows the truth."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6ICLcC2vy0Ym"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Step 1 — Simulate data**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "aWavJihW666k"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "set.seed(123)\n",
        "\n",
        "n <- 50  # participants per group\n",
        "\n",
        "# baseline ability\n",
        "baseline_treatment <- rnorm(n, mean = 50, sd = 10)\n",
        "baseline_control   <- rnorm(n, mean = 50, sd = 10)\n",
        "\n",
        "# PRACTICE EFFECT (everyone improves just by repeating task)\n",
        "practice_effect <- 5\n",
        "\n",
        "# TRUE training effect (set to 0 → intervention actually does nothing)\n",
        "true_training_effect <- 0\n",
        "\n",
        "# post scores\n",
        "post_treatment <- baseline_treatment + practice_effect + true_training_effect + rnorm(n,0,3)\n",
        "post_control   <- baseline_control + practice_effect + rnorm(n,0,3)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XU9qC7BSviE8"
      },
      "execution_count": 4,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Step 2 — What happens with NO control group (bad design)**\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kIASMQAkyDqY"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "t.test(post_treatment, baseline_treatment, paired = TRUE)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WZEpQWo2vwna",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 208
        },
        "outputId": "cd778f98-30aa-4f73-c7ce-b6365973e04c"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "\n",
              "\tPaired t-test\n",
              "\n",
              "data:  post_treatment and baseline_treatment\n",
              "t = 10.097, df = 49, p-value = 1.458e-13\n",
              "alternative hypothesis: true mean difference is not equal to 0\n",
              "95 percent confidence interval:\n",
              " 3.394802 5.081795\n",
              "sample estimates:\n",
              "mean difference \n",
              "       4.238299 \n"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Step 3 — Add a proper control group (good design)**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "RENdjp44yJ8m"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "change_treatment <- post_treatment - baseline_treatment\n",
        "change_control   <- post_control - baseline_control\n",
        "\n",
        "t.test(change_treatment, change_control)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "j2Q6pHYCvw5_",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 208
        },
        "outputId": "e56e8dda-d968-4d2a-e42a-182f3f67502c"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "\n",
              "\tWelch Two Sample t-test\n",
              "\n",
              "data:  change_treatment and change_control\n",
              "t = -1.5236, df = 97.64, p-value = 0.1308\n",
              "alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0\n",
              "95 percent confidence interval:\n",
              " -2.0219395  0.2656959\n",
              "sample estimates:\n",
              "mean of x mean of y \n",
              " 4.238299  5.116421 \n"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Step 4 — Visualise**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "By4u4-2nyYwC"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "boxplot(change_treatment, change_control,\n",
        "        names = c(\"Treatment\", \"Control\"),\n",
        "        ylab = \"Improvement\",\n",
        "        main = \"Both groups improve equally → practice effect\")\n",
        "abline(h = 0, lty = 2)\n"
      ],
