    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Conclusion:\n",
        "Control and experimental conditions should be comparable in design and differ only in the manipulated variable to ensure valid causal conclusions."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mJSt4397GDMD"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 1.2. Inadequate comparisons"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FT7oLDqF5tXO"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Imagine we want to test whether an intervention changes the relationship between two variables in two groups.\n",
        "\n",
        "*   In Group A the effect is significant.\n",
        "*   In Group B the effect is not significant.\n",
        "\n",
        "We might wrongly conclude the effects differ.\n",
        "But when we directly compare them, they do not differ."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FVgb-gbr5-I7"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Imagine we measure the correlation between motivation (X) and performance (Y) in two groups:\n",
        "\n",
        "Group A → correlation is significant\n",
        "\n",
        "Group B → correlation is not significant\n",
        "\n",
        "Can we conclude the relationship is stronger in Group A?\n",
        "\n",
        "Let’s simulate."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dBlAF76I6NfG"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Step 1 — Simulate two groups with SAME true correlation**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kO1R86Oj7NeO"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "set.seed(42)\n",
        "\n",
        "n <- 30\n",
        "\n",
        "# Same true slope\n",
        "beta <- 0.4\n",
        "\n",
        "# Group A (lower noise → significant)\n",
        "xA <- rnorm(n)\n",
        "yA <- beta * xA + rnorm(n, sd = 0.8)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Group B (higher noise → often non-significant)\n",
        "xB <- rnorm(n)\n",
        "yB <- beta * xB + rnorm(n, sd = 1.5)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ZVnWaPFu6JJo"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Step 2 — Separate analyses**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mafPj8OO7iTF"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "summary(lm(yA ~ xA))\n",
        "summary(lm(yB ~ xB))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 607
        },
        "id": "0Acojfhb7lDe",
        "outputId": "0b445534-4234-4bef-eac5-15914550deb1"
